entry.title: webgl: Fix chromeos low latency canvas resource SkColorType
entry.content:
https://crrev.com/c/4553796 made the ColorBuffer format match the one

means the format seen by ExportLowLatencyCanvasResource can be BGRX_8888

which isn't handled in that function currently. This CL fixes that by

using viz::ToClosestSkColorType which maps color buffer format BGRX_8888

to kRGB_888x_SkColorType and matches the previous behavior of RBGX_8888.

entry.title: jinx: fix prediction suggestion tracking
entry.content:
Currently tracking of prediction suggestions is incorrect when the first

character of a suggestion is not typed by the user. This is due to a bug

in the current tracking logic where the MultiWordSuggester does not

enter tracking mode when a prediction suggestion is initially shown.



This CL fixes this logic with the new stale suggestion handling logic

added in crrev/c/4520736. With stale suggestions handled, we then know

that any prediction suggestion received should simply be appended to the

current surrounding text. Thus we can transition the suggester straight

to tracking mode without needing to reconcile the current surrounding

text with the suggestion given.

entry.title: saved_desks: Fix excessive repainting in the library
entry.content:
This CL fixes excessive repainting in the saved desk library. Prior to

this CL, just moving the cursor around in the saved desk library would

cause the entire library to be repainted.



If the cursor is moved to hover over a saved desk item, we fade in the

button to launch the template. It is positioned in the same spot as the

icons for the saved desk, so those fade out. In the old implementation,

once the icons had faded out, we would call SetVisibility on the icon

container view. This in turn triggered the containing flex layout, which

eventually results in a lot of stuff getting laid out again, which then

ends up re-painting things.



This change makes it so that the two views (the icon container and the

hover container) are always "visible". We instead modify the opacity on

the containers as needed to hide and show them. With this change in

place, no `Layout` calls happen when moving the cursor around.



BUG=b:281880456

entry.title: Migrate calls from SkSurface::flush -> GrDirectContext::flush
entry.content:
Presently, SkSurface::flush() defers to the GrDirectContext used

to create the surface to send work to the GPU. As part of an effort

to decouple SkSurface from the GPU code, we want to explicitly

call flush on the GrDirectContext and remove flushing from Surfaces.

http://review.skia.org/698237



In migrating these APIs, I tried to track where that context was

and use it directly and explicitly. In cases where that was not

obvious, I fell back to the existing behavior of "extract

GrRecordingContext, cast to GrDirectContext, check if it is non-null

(e.g. Raster or Graphite surfaces), and then call flush". In cases

where the default flush options were used, the helper

skgpu::ganesh::Flush() was used.



One peculiarity I found was in skia_output_device_dawn.cc where

the surfaces made in that file appear to be Graphite-backed

(and thus calling flush is a no-op), but when I removed that flush,

tests broke. So, I kept flushing in that spot.

entry.title: Disable usage of `__is_cpp17_contiguous_iterator` until libc++ rolls.
entry.content:
Though names prefixed with `__` are reserved for implementation use,

specializing `__is_cpp17_contiguous_iterator` is currently the only way

to tell libc++ that `memcpy()` can be safe to use with a custom

iterator. Without this workaround, there are noticeable regressions,

e.g. when using std::copy() with spans of trivially copyable types (see

https://crbug.com/994174).



However, https://reviews.llvm.org/D150801 renames this template to

`__libcpp_is_contiguous_iterator`, which blocks rolling past this libc++

revision. As a workaround, temporarily forward declare and specialize

both variants.

`

In addition, C++20 provides an official way for a custom iterator to opt

into these types of optimizations, using `iterator_concept`, so also go

ahead and opt `CheckedContiguousIterator` into using this.

entry.title: Fix NOTREACHED when setting automatic downloads to ALLOW_ALL_DOWNLOADS
entry.content:
I noticed a bug within the automatic downloads flow: when the setting

is changed to ALLOW_ALL_DOWNLOADS via the dialog, the icon remains in

the omnibox. However, it shows an empty dialog when clicked. This

happens because we're hitting the NOTREACHED in

ContentSettingDownloadsBubbleModel::SetRadioGroup(). This is causing

crashes in Edge, hence the need to fix.



This CL makes sure that we don't erase the status in

OnUserInteraction() when it is ALLOW_ALL_DOWNLOADS. We reset the status

until DidFinishNavigation(). This renders a dialog with the options to

continue accepting or block automatic downloads.



Repro steps:

1) Navigate to a website with an automatic download.

2) Set automatic downloads to "Don't allow".

3) Try to download, it is blocked.

4) Select "Always allow" in dialog.

5) Download file.

6) Open dialog, see that content is empty.
